---
const latest = await import('../../../public/reports/latest-candidate.json');
const index = await import('../../../public/reports/index.json');
const result = latest.default.result;
const metadata = latest.default.metadata;
const runs = index.default;
const candidates = runs.filter((run) => run.report_kind === 'candidate');
const experiments = runs.filter((run) => run.report_kind === 'experiment');
const score = Number(result.scoring.final_score).toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 });
const p99Score = Number(result.scoring.p99_score.value).toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 });
const detectionScore = Number(result.scoring.detection_score.value).toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 });
---

<section class="stats-grid">
  <div class="stat-box">
    <div class="stat-label">Latest p99</div>
    <div class="stat-value">{result.p99}</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">GitHub Actions runner</div>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-box danger">
    <div class="stat-label">Failures</div>
    <div class="stat-value">{result.scoring.failure_rate}</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">Target is 0%</div>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-box warning">
    <div class="stat-label">Score</div>
    <div class="stat-value">{score}</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">Official-like, not official hardware</div>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-box">
    <div class="stat-label">Archived runs</div>
    <div class="stat-value">{candidates.length}</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">{experiments.length} experiments separated</div>
  </div>
</section>

<h2 class="section-title">SYSTEM TOPOLOGY</h2>
<section class="scenarios">
  <div class="scenario-card">
    <h3>Transport Path</h3>
    <div class="endpoint"><span class="method get">GET</span> /ready</div>
    <p>nginx stream accepts port 9999 and forwards raw HTTP to two API containers through Unix Domain Sockets. The app parses enough HTTP/1 to satisfy the Rinha workload.</p>
    <div class="progress-container">
      <div class="progress-label">Latency path [||||||||||||||||||..] tuned</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="scenario-card">
    <h3>Fraud Decision</h3>
    <div class="endpoint"><span class="method post">POST</span> /fraud-score</div>
    <p>Manual JSON parsing extracts only the required fields, vectorizes into 14 dimensions, scores with rounded int16 IVF, and writes one prebuilt HTTP response.</p>
    <div class="progress-container">
      <div class="progress-label danger-text">p99 gap [|||||...............] active</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="stress-tests">
  <h3>OFFICIAL-LIKE BENCHMARK STREAM</h3>
  <p class="stress-intro">
    Candidate metrics use the default submission stack. Proxy/search overlays are archived as experiments so failed probes never become the displayed latest candidate.
  </p>

  <div class="stress-metrics">
    <div class="stress-metric">
      <span class="metric-value">{p99Score}</span>
      <span class="metric-label">p99 score</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stress-metric">
      <span class="metric-value">{detectionScore}</span>
      <span class="metric-label">detection score</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stress-metric">
      <span class="metric-value">{result.scoring.breakdown.http_errors}</span>
      <span class="metric-label">HTTP errors</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="stress-links">
    <a href="./reports/" class="stress-link">View report history</a>
    <a href={metadata.run_url} class="stress-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Latest CI run</a>
    <a href="https://rinhadebackend.com.br/" class="stress-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Public ranking</a>
  </div>
</section>
